headline: Southwest: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: DALLAS (AP) — Southwest Airlines Co. (LUV) on Wednesday reported second-quarter net income of $213 million. On a per-share basis, the Dallas-based company said it had profit of 39 cents. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs, came to 43 cents per share.

headline: Southwest Airlines earnings hit by weak US travel demand
summary: CHICAGO (Reuters) -Southwest Airlines reported lower-than-expected quarterly profit and revenue on Wednesday, hurt by tepid demand from U.S. consumers for travel.  Lingering uncertainty about the broader economy due to President Donald Trump's trade war and rising living costs has hurt carriers that primarily service the U.S. domestic market and price-sensitive customers.  The Texas-based airline said domestic leisure travel demand  stabilized after a slump in March and April and was showing signs of improvement.
